      "rationale": "All load steps converged to force residual < 5e-5. Energy balance error < 0.1% across all 11 simulation cases. No divergence or negative pivot warnings recorded."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by qualified engineer not involved in model construction; checklist-based review documented.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a senior computational engineer using the DePuy Synthes FEA model review checklist (Form FEA-QA-07). All 42 checklist items confirmed. Review documented in peer review record PR-NC-001."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model physics (linear elastic, small deformation) justified for the load regime; contact formulation validated against known reference cases.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive model appropriate for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) below yield. ASTM F1717 test loads remain below yield in the elastic regime for stiffness QoI. Augmented Lagrange contact formulation validated against Hertzian contact benchmark. Geometric nonlinearity included for large-displacement loading arm."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of production lot material; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114.5 GPa) and Poisson ratio (0.342) from tensile coupon testing of the same production lot used for bench specimens. UHMWPE block modulus from compressive coupon data. Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements on three representative specimens. Dimensional variability < 0.3% CV."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 specimens tested; specimens sourced from production-representative lot; traceability to device design history file confirmed.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). All specimens from the same production lot (Lot NC-2021-047) with full traceability to device DHF. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness = 3.8%, confirming reproducibility."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate physiological loading environment including relevant boundary conditions, loading rate, and environmental conditions.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 protocol followed at ambient temperature (22°C ± 2°C) and quasi-static loading rate (25 mm/min). Single loading condition tested; physiological loading rate variation and temperature effects not explored. Achieved level limited to 2 due to single test condition. This deficiency is acknowledged and accepted given medium model risk level and corroborating analytical evidence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and material inputs demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions; differences quantified and propagated as uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Experimental boundary conditions (pin-pin loading frame, UHMWPE block embedment depth, loading axis offset) replicated in FEA with measured tolerances. Uncertainty in boundary condition positioning (±0.5 mm) propagated via sensitivity analysis; contribution to QoI uncertainty < 1.5%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Eq. (5-1) incorporating simulation numerical uncertainty (unum), input uncertainty (uinput), and experimental uncertainty (uexp). Results: stiffness E/uval = 0.83 (4.7% diff), yield force E/uval = 1.12 (6.1% diff), force at 40 mm E/uval = 0.61 (3.2% diff). All within acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements; mapping to COU decision documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. Each QoI maps directly to a clinical failure mode (subsidence, fatigue fracture, gross deformation). QoI-to-COU mapping documented in credibility plan CP-NC-001."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario matches COU geometry, loading, and material with documented similarity argument.",
      "rationale": "Validation activity uses production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs under ASTM F1717 compression-bending — identical to the COU. No extrapolation in geometry, material, or loading mode required. Similarity argument documented in validation plan VP-NC-001, reviewed and approved by regulatory affairs."
    }
